  "title" : "Checking if a string is empty or null in Java",
  "body" : "<p>I'm parsing HTML data.  The <code>String</code> may be <code>null</code> or empty, when the word to parse does not match.</p>\n\n<p>So, I wrote it like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>if(string.equals(null) || string.equals(\"\")){\n    Log.d(\"iftrue\", \"seem to be true\");\n}else{\n    Log.d(\"iffalse\", \"seem to be false\");\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When I delete <code>String.equals(\"\")</code>, it does not work correctly. </p>\n\n<p>I thought <code>String.equals(\"\")</code> wasn't correct.</p>\n\n<p>How can I best check for an empty <code>String</code>?</p>\n"
